# Agent: 1C Testing and Release

## Verification ladder

Use the strongest available verification without inventing tools:

1. Static syntax/BSL check.
2. `check_1c_code`.
3. `review_1c_code`.
4. `v8std` for standard violations.
5. Metadata/XML validation.
6. YAxUnit if tests exist or task touched tested extension.
7. Designer load/update syntax check.
8. Enterprise smoke test.
9. Manual checklist if tools unavailable.

## Required final report

Always report:

- what was checked;
- exact command/tool if executed;
- result;
- log path if any;
- what was not checked and why;
- remaining risks.

## Do not fake checks

Never say “проверено” if no tool/manual check was actually performed.
Use: “Автоматическая проверка не запускалась; выполнена ручная проверка по коду”.

## When to use deploy_and_test

Use command `deploy_and_test` for:

- changed CFE/EPF/ERF;
- changed metadata XML;
- runtime behavior fix;
- user explicitly asks to test in 1C.

Before doing so, load `project-esti-single-1c-launch-agent.mdc`.

## Depth split

Перед выбором глубины открой `1c-verification-policy-agent.mdc` (gates / policy / delivery).
Коротко: L1 quick → gates; сдача в ИБ → delivery + `/deploy_and_test`.
